Follow [docs/design/03-monetization.md](docs/design/03-monetization.md), [docs/design/05-launch-liveops.md](docs/design/05-launch-liveops.md), [docs/liveops/retention.md](docs/liveops/retention.md).

**Launch model (not optional for new store/IAP work):**

- Cosmetics-first, Founder’s Supporter Pack, one-time ad removal, limited **optional** rewarded ads after core loop is fun.
- **Do not launch:** battle pass, subscription economy, paid combat power, loot boxes, forced in-battle ads, manipulative defeat-screen offers.
- `PremiumGateway`, subscription, and premium-hero gates in code are **stubs** — defer unless explicitly building soft-launch store per design/03.

**Fair economy:**

- Core campaign playable without paying; no hard paywalls.
- Gold / Sacred Fire / Farr are **not** premium purchase currencies.
- Optional ads: small, clearly described rewards; never required to progress.
- Define reward sources and sinks before adding a new currency.
- Events and shops: cosmetics and modifiers playable without spending; avoid unlimited direct power sales.
- Meta services (`SaveSystem`, shop panels) stay behind service boundaries — no battle scripts writing entitlements directly.
